All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ArrivalProcess
Class representing the arrival process of events.
Car
Represents a car in the simulation.
Clock
Singleton class representing a clock to keep track of simulation time.
Customer
Represents a customer in the simulation.
Engine
The Engine class manages the simulation, including the clock, event list, and simulation control.
Event
Class representing an event in the simulation.
EventList
Class representing a list of events, managed as a priority queue.
EventType
Enum representing the different types of events in the simulation.
IEventType
Interface representing the type of an event in the simulation.
Main
The main method serves as the entry point for the application.
MyEngine
The MyEngine class extends the Engine class and simulates a gas station with multiple service points.
RandomChooserForCustomer
Outputs the results of the simulation, including various performance metrics.
RandomChooserForRouter
The RandomChooserForRouter class is responsible for randomly selecting the next event type based on predefined probabilities for each event type.
Result
The Result class provides methods to calculate and generate results for the gas station simulation.
Router
The Router class is responsible for managing the queue of customers and routing them to the next event.
ServicePoint
The ServicePoint class represents a service point in the gas station simulation.
Simulator
 
SimulatorController
Controller class for the simulator.
SimulatorView
The SimulatorView class is the main entry point for the JavaFX application.
Trace
The Trace class provides logging functionality for the simulation.
Trace.Level
Enum representing the trace levels.
